.TH "tb_cfg_reset" 9 "tb_cfg_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_cfg_reset \- send a reset packet and wait for a response
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tb_cfg_result" tb_cfg_reset
.BI "(struct tb_ctl *ctl "  ","
.BI "u64 route "  ","
.BI "int timeout_msec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctl" 12
Control channel pointer
.IP "route" 12
Router string for the router to send reset
.IP "timeout_msec" 12
Timeout in ms how long to wait for the response
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the switch at route is incorrectly configured then we will not receive a
reply (even though the switch will reset). The caller should check for
-ETIMEDOUT and attempt to reconfigure the switch.
